        "label": "EAN-Search API token",
        "generateUrl": "https://www.ean-search.org/ean-database-api.html",
        "setup": "Create an account from the [EAN Database Accounts page](https://www.ean-search.org/ean-database-api.html) using one of the `Create ... Account` links, then log in to your EAN-Search account to obtain your private API access token. The docs say to replace `abcdef` in examples with your own token after opening an account, and the same regular API token is used for GraphQL."
      },
      "ean_oauth_client": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "EAN-Search OAuth client",
        "generateUrl": "https://www.ean-search.org/register",
        "setup": "Register an OAuth client against EAN-Search using the dynamic client registration endpoint at [register](https://www.ean-search.org/register). Then run the OAuth flow against [authorize](https://www.ean-search.org/authorize) and [token](https://www.ean-search.org/token). The catalog indicates the `user` scope is supported. Use this when connecting to the MCP server, which the docs say handles authorization via your account."
      }
